   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Harvard_604742_1847_04_07_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <note>To D Hodgeson Esq</note>
               <lb/>
               <dateline>
                  <placeName>Edgeworths Town</placeName>
                  <lb/>
                  <date when="1847-04-07"/>Apr. 7 1847</dateline>
               <lb/>
               <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
               <lb/>
            </opener>
            <p>
                    I am gratified by your<lb/>
                    being convinced that I should<lb/>
                    not think it any trouble to<lb/>
                    make any inquiry that can<lb/>
                    be useful to any distressed<lb/>
                    person and especially to one<lb/>
                    of any of my countrywomen and<lb/>
                    moreover the daughter of<lb/>
                    an old tenant<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>I have strictly observed<lb/>
                    your injunction not to open,<lb/>
                    then<lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Harvard_604742_1847_04_07_page02.jpg"/>
                        
                    mention the <choice>
                  <orig>s<del/>ubject</orig>
                  <reg>subject</reg>
               </choice> to any<lb/>
                        one, except to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
                    (who is the same as myself)<lb/>
                    and to whom the poor<lb/>
                    girl herself refers - You<lb/>
                    and she may be assured<lb/>
                        that neither through <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2">
                  <unclear>Mrs</unclear> E</persName>
               <lb/>
                    or myself shall it transpire<lb/>
                    that any inquiry has been<lb/>
                    made, nor shall it through<lb/>
                    us be known to her friends<lb/>
                        that she is at <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Liverpool_ENK">Liverpool</placeName> -<lb/>
               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Harvard_604742_1847_04_07_page03.jpg"/>
                        
                    Her mother was here <choice>
                  <orig>yes-<lb/>
                        terday</orig>
                  <reg>yesterday</reg>
               </choice> inquiring if <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> E</persName>
               <lb/>
                    knew where she is - And<lb/>
                    fearing that she must be<lb/>
                    dead as she has not heard<lb/>
                    from her for a long time -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Edgeworth</persName> is writing<lb/>
                    to you herself, and she could<lb/>
                    give you all the information<lb/>
                    she can - I know nothing<lb/>
                    of the girls story, but what<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2">Mrs E</persName> has told me -<lb/>
               <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_Harvard_604742_1847_04_07_page04.jpg"/>
                    
                    I beg to add that if at<lb/>
                    any future time I can<lb/>
                    be of service in making<lb/>
                    any inquiries for your<lb/>
                    benevolent purposes, I<lb/>
                    shall think it no trouble<lb/>
                    to make them even if they<lb/>
               <unclear>should</unclear> not concern any<lb/>
                    of our own people - It<lb/>
                    will be a gratification to me<lb/>
                    to answer to your good <unclear>opinion</unclear>
               <lb/>
                    of<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
                        Yours truly<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
         </div>
